{"session_id":"svc-1778088325815585642","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-06T17:25:27.916636697Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-259bb4e2-20260506T172523-0e09eeeb","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260506T172523-0e09eeeb/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260506T172523-0e09eeeb/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260506T172523-0e09eeeb/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260506T172523-0e09eeeb/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260506T172523-0e09eeeb/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead description and AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and conservative project defaults (YAGNI, DOWITYTD, no-docs-unless-asked) in this worktree — write whatever the bead asks for.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-259bb4e2\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eagent: cleanly unwind interrupted work and try attempts\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;After the root context is cancelled by Ctrl-C/SIGTERM, `ddx work` and `ddx try` must finish the TD-031 interruption path: preserve available evidence, classify the attempt as mechanically disrupted, release any non-terminal bead claim, remove runtime liveness state, and leave the unfinished bead re-claimable. The current code has partial context-cancellation classification but needs explicit end-to-end coverage for the CLI work/try paths.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:859-878 marks non-success reports as disrupted when ctx is cancelled, but the surrounding cleanup/unclaim behavior is only incidentally covered by generic failure branches.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:812-846 starts and stops claim heartbeat around an attempt; interrupted attempts must stop liveness and release or clear claims deterministically.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:797-807 creates a dispatch context and only the bead-extra cancel path forces `operator_cancel`; plain context cancellation should remain `signal`/mechanical disruption, not `operator_cancel`.\u0026#xA;- cli/cmd/try.go:333-342 and cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go:1921-1940 propagate `cmd.Context()` into worker.Run but need regression tests that cancellation leaves the target bead re-claimable and reports the signal path.\u0026#xA;- docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-031-bead-state-machine.md:289-314 defines the claim release and no-cooldown requirements for worker shutdown/interruption.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Make interrupted attempts produce a stable disrupted/interrupted report reason (for example `context_canceled` / `signal`) without counting as model no-progress.\u0026#xA;- Ensure the loop unclaims interrupted non-terminal beads and removes any external claim heartbeat/liveness record.\u0026#xA;- Ensure interrupted attempts do not set `execute-loop-retry-after` unless a separate retryable condition was already recorded before cancellation.\u0026#xA;- Ensure `ddx try \u0026lt;id\u0026gt;` reports a clear interrupted outcome and exits non-zero after cleanup.\u0026#xA;- Add regression tests around worker.Run plus command-level try/work cancellation paths using controllable fake executors/runners.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Do not preserve worktrees as resumable by default. Cleanup/retry-from-scratch is the reliable default.\u0026#xA;- Do not alter operator cancel-marker semantics (`cancel-requested` / `operator_cancel`).\u0026#xA;- Do not change successful landing/review behavior when cancellation arrives after a terminal mutation.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. TestWorkInterrupt_InFlightAttemptUnclaimsBead verifies cancelling the work command context during an in-flight attempt releases the claim and leaves the bead open/re-claimable.\u0026#xA;2. TestWorkInterrupt_DoesNotSetNoProgressCooldown verifies interrupted work does not set `execute-loop-retry-after` or increment no-progress suppression.\u0026#xA;3. TestWorkInterrupt_RemovesClaimLiveness verifies external claim heartbeat/liveness is removed or stale-safe after cleanup.\u0026#xA;4. TestTryInterrupt_InFlightAttemptUnclaimsTarget verifies `ddx try \u0026lt;id\u0026gt;` cancellation leaves the target bead re-claimable and exits non-zero with an interrupted/signal-class outcome.\u0026#xA;5. TestTryInterrupt_DoesNotReportOperatorCancel verifies plain context cancellation is not classified as `operator_cancel` unless the bead cancel marker was present.\u0026#xA;6. TestInterruptedAfterTerminalMutation_DoesNotUndoClose verifies cancellation after a successful terminal mutation does not reopen or unclaim a closed bead.\u0026#xA;7. `rg -n \u0026#34;context.Canceled|context_canceled|signal|operator_cancel|execute-loop-retry-after\u0026#34; cli/internal/agent cli/cmd` shows cancellation paths are explicit and comments distinguish signal interruption from operator cancel.\u0026#xA;8. `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./cmd/... ./internal/agent/... ./internal/bead/... -run \u0026#34;TestWorkInterrupt|TestTryInterrupt|TestInterrupted|TestCancel|TestClaim\u0026#34; -count=1` passes.\u0026#xA;9. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:agent, area:beads, area:cli, kind:bug, reliability, spec:FEAT-010, spec:TD-031, interrupt\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-99a3be32\" spec-id=\"FEAT-010\" base-rev=\"278562820307c6dc13cbe116ebcd9bc931cd56b3\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260506T172523-0e09eeeb\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"FEAT-010\" path=\"docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-task-execution.md\"\u003eFeature: Task Execution\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"attempt_id":"20260506T172523-0e09eeeb","base_rev":"278562820307c6dc13cbe116ebcd9bc931cd56b3","bead_id":"ddx-259bb4e2","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260506T172523-0e09eeeb","correlation_id":"ddx-259bb4e2:20260506T172523-0e09eeeb","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260506T172523-0e09eeeb/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"f3dcf90b259c31500051aef56d40cacfe16a3166d18064074d34309523b3980e","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-c5b765cd","worker_id":""}}}
